snippet.textDisplay:
I'm 53 years old and struggled with depression and alcoholism for 24 years, after I was brutally raped and cut with a knife by a 17 year old boy (man), who broke into my home, and waited for me inside my closet. He stalked me, for two weeks, while siding the neighbors house in 1996.
I was 34 years old at the time of the assault. The struggles I survived are countless. Suicide attempts, moving 26 times in 24 years, trying to find that safe place again. Today, I'm Sober 1 year. THANK YOU LORD! THIS SONG TOUCHED MY HEART, TO THE POINT I COULD RELATE TO DEMI'S PAIN, through this performance. I felt just like her. For years I felt trapped inside my self. I cried out to The Lord too. Please send me anyone. He answered my prayers finally, it was ME I was needing back. I pray for this BEAUTIFUL Soul, that she finds peace and love. GOD BLESS YOU DEAREST DEMI, you will be a part of my prayer list every night. 😇😇❤💛

God bless her.

snippet.textDisplay: Great song. Great lyrics. And Demi has always been a great (and overlooked talent in the industry).... But, she is very clearly sharp for a surprising amount of the song, especially during the chorus. I’m confused as to how no one has mentioned hearing it. Are people tone deaf? And, no, her being emotional would not be the valid excuse for this off-key singing. 🤨 1:50 It’s literally making me cringe, and it’s consistent throughout. It kinda ruined an otherwise wonderful performance for me.
